Lautaro Martinez with his goals and positioning in the opponent’s box has managed to catch the eye of several of Europe’s top dogs. The 22-year-old has already bagged 16 goals from 26 appearances in the Serie A and the Champions League. READ ALSO:  Senegalese defender joins Dutch side FC Utrecht Both Manchester United and Barcelona have already shown interest according to reports, and, with Chelsea in the look for a frontman, Lautaro has been identified as a target. While Lyon’s Moussa Dembele and RB Leipzig’s Timo Werner have been linked with a switch to Stamford Bridge, Calciomercato claims that the Blues are contemplating a bid for Martinez. Despite Inter wishing to keep hold of the Argentina international, a release clause, said to be in the region of £94m, means that the player could attract offers in the summer.